        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks AD for his article in <hi rend="italic">Das Ausland</hi> ["Englische Kritiker und Anti-Kritiker über den Darwinismus", 49 (1871): 1153–7].</p>  
<p>Mivart’s book [<hi rend="italic">Genesis of species</hi>], which misinterprets CD’s views, has produced a great effect in England.</p>  
<p>He has answered the point about incipient structures being useless in new [6th] edition of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>.</p>  
<p>His <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> has had immense circulation, but has met with approval of hardly any naturalists. He supposes it was a mistake to publish it, but it will pave way for a better work.</p> 
        </abstract>
